<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB02839</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING CIVIL SERVICE ELIGIBILITY TO GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES, UNDER CERTAIN CONDITIONS, WHOSE STATUS OF APPOINTMENT IS EITHER CASUAL OR CONTRACTUAL AND WHO HAVE RENDERED A TOTAL OF FIVE YEARS OF EFFICIENT SERVICE</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Grants civil service eligibility to government employees, under certain conditions, whose status of appointment is either casual or contractual who have rendered a total of at least five (5) years of efficient service.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BAGUILAT, TEDDY JR. BRAWNER</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-08-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2016-08-17</td></tr></table>